{
  "description": "A wide-angle shot captures a dramatic coastal scene featuring the Golden Gate Bridge shrouded in a thick layer of fog. The bridge, painted a vibrant orange-red, spans across the expansive body of water, its towers partially obscured by the low-hanging clouds. Waves roll towards the shore, creating white foam against the dark, rocky coastline. In the background, rolling hills and distant landmasses are visible, also partially veiled in mist. The sky is predominantly gray and overcast, creating a moody and atmospheric ambiance. Foreground elements include dark, wet rocks and some green vegetation. The overall impression is one of raw natural power and iconic architectural grandeur.",
